<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 3:57AM CDT  by NWS Eastern ND and Grand Forks</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Grand
Forks, northern Nelson, east central Ramsey and southwestern Walsh
Counties through 430 AM CDT...
At 357 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Petersburg, or 39 miles southwest of Grafton, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lakota, Michigan, Petersburg, Dahlen, Brocket, Niagara and Whitman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
